                <ns0:archetype_id><ns0:value>openEHR-EHR-EVALUATION.problem_diagnosis.v1</ns0:value></ns0:archetype_id><ns0:term_definitions code="at0077"><ns0:items id="description">Geschatte of precieze datum/tijd dat de eerste tekenen of symptomen van het probleem of de diagnose werden opgemerkt.</ns0:items><ns0:items id="text">Datum/tijd van aanvang</ns0:items></ns0:term_definitions><ns0:term_definitions code="at0076"><ns0:items id="description">*The diagnosis has been confirmed against recognised criteria.(en)</ns0:items><ns0:items id="text">*Confirmed(en)</ns0:items></ns0:term_definitions><ns0:term_definitions code="at0075"><ns0:items id="description">*The diagnosis has been identified with a high level of certainty.(en)</ns0:items><ns0:items id="text">*Probable(en)</ns0:items></ns0:term_definitions><ns0:term_definitions code="at0074"><ns0:items id="description">*The diagnosis has been identified with a low level of certainty.(en)</ns0:items><ns0:items id="text">*Suspected(en)</ns0:items></ns0:term_definitions><ns0:term_definitions code="at0073"><ns0:items id="description">*The level of confidence in the identification of the diagnosis.(en)</ns0:items><ns0:items id="text">*Diagnostic certainty(en)</ns0:items></ns0:term_definitions><ns0:term_definitions code="at0072"><ns0:items id="description">*Narrative description about the course of the problem or diagnosis since onset.(en)</ns0:items><ns0:items id="text">*Course description(en)</ns0:items></ns0:term_definitions><ns0:term_definitions code="at0071"><ns0:items id="description">*Additional information required to capture local content or to align with other reference models/formalisms.(en)</ns0:items><ns0:items id="text">*Extension(en)</ns0:items></ns0:term_definitions><ns0:term_definitions code="at0070"><ns0:items id="description">*The date this problem or diagnosis was last updated.(en)</ns0:items><ns0:items id="text">*Last updated(en)</ns0:items></ns0:term_definitions><ns0:term_definitions code="at0069"><ns0:items id="description">*Additional narrative about the problem or diagnosis not captured in other fields.(en)</ns0:items><ns0:items id="text">*Comment(en)</ns0:items></ns0:term_definitions><ns0:term_definitions code="at0049"><ns0:items id="description">*The problem or diagnosis prevents normal activity or will seriously damage health if left untreated.(en)</ns0:items><ns0:items id="text">*Severe(en)</ns0:items></ns0:term_definitions><ns0:term_definitions code="at0048"><ns0:items id="description">*The problem or diagnosis causes interference with normal activity or will damage health if left untreated.(en)</ns0:items><ns0:items id="text">*Moderate(en)</ns0:items></ns0:term_definitions><ns0:term_definitions code="at0047"><ns0:items id="description">*The problem or diagnosis does not interfere with normal activity or may cause damage to health if left untreated.(en)</ns0:items><ns0:items id="text">*Mild(en)</ns0:items></ns0:term_definitions><ns0:term_definitions code="at0046"><ns0:items id="description">*Structured details for location-, domain-, episode- or workflow-specific aspects of the diagnostic process.(en)</ns0:items><ns0:items id="text">*Status(en)</ns0:items></ns0:term_definitions><ns0:term_definitions code="at0043"><ns0:items id="description">*Details that are additionally required to record as unique attributes of this problem or diagnosis.(en)</ns0:items><ns0:items id="text">*Specific details(en)</ns0:items></ns0:term_definitions><ns0:term_definitions code="at0039"><ns0:items id="description">*A structured anatomical location for the problem or diagnosis.(en)</ns0:items><ns0:items id="text">*Structured body site(en)</ns0:items></ns0:term_definitions><ns0:term_definitions code="at0032"><ns0:items id="description">*@ internal @(en)</ns0:items><ns0:items id="text">*Tree(en)</ns0:items></ns0:term_definitions><ns0:term_definitions code="at0030"><ns0:items id="description">*Estimated or actual date/time of resolution or remission for this problem or diagnosis, as determined by a healthcare professional.(en)</ns0:items><ns0:items id="text">*Date/time of resolution(en)</ns0:items></ns0:term_definitions><ns0:term_definitions code="at0012"><ns0:items id="description">Identificatie van een eenvoudig lichaamsdeel voor de lokatie van het probleem of de diagnose.</ns0:items><ns0:items id="text">Lichaamsdeel</ns0:items></ns0:term_definitions><ns0:term_definitions code="at0009"><ns0:items id="description">Verhalende beschrijving van het probleem of de diagnose.</ns0:items><ns0:items id="text">Klinische beschrijving</ns0:items></ns0:term_definitions><ns0:term_definitions code="at0005"><ns0:items id="description">*An assessment of the overall severity of the problem or diagnosis.(en)</ns0:items><ns0:items id="text">*Severity(en)</ns0:items></ns0:term_definitions><ns0:term_definitions code="at0003"><ns0:items id="description">Geschatte of werkelijke datum/tijd waarop het probleem of de diagnose is herkend door een zorgprofessional.</ns0:items><ns0:items id="text">Datum/tijd van klinische herkenning</ns0:items></ns0:term_definitions><ns0:term_definitions code="at0002"><ns0:items id="description">Identificatie van het probleem of de diagnose bij naam.
                            </ns0:items><ns0:items id="text">Naam van het probleem / de diagnose</ns0:items></ns0:term_definitions><ns0:term_definitions code="at0001"><ns0:items id="description">*@ internal @(en)</ns0:items><ns0:items id="text">*structure(en)</ns0:items></ns0:term_definitions><ns0:term_definitions code="at0000"><ns0:items id="description">Informatie over een enkele vast te stellen medische aandoening, een letsel, beperking of andere zaak die invloed heeft op de fysieke, mentale en/of het sociale welbevinden van een individu.</ns0:items><ns0:items id="text">Probleem/Diagnose</ns0:items></ns0:term_definitions><ns0:term_definitions code="at0078"><ns0:items id="description">*A cause, set of causes, or manner of causation of the problem or diagnosis.(en)</ns0:items><ns0:items id="text">*Cause (en)</ns0:items></ns0:term_definitions><ns0:term_definitions code="at0079"><ns0:items id="description">*Specific variant or subtype of the Diagnosis, if relevant. (en)</ns0:items><ns0:items id="text">*Variant (en)</ns0:items></ns0:term_definitions><ns0:term_definitions code="at0080"><ns0:items id="description" /><ns0:items id="text">*DV_TEXT (en)</ns0:items></ns0:term_definitions></ns0:children>
